        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Greetings Dark Ones!</P><P>I go my new necro to 16 (very fun) and was wondering about my pet and giving him weapons. I have heard that weapons increase dmg output of pets, and that weapons dont. Could someone clarify this for me?</P><P>Also, I was thinking that IF pets could do more dmg with a weapon, why couldnt they make it so that if/when your pet dies you could loot his corpse to get that weapon back? It would be cool to give a pet a Centi LS or something that helped him to really put a beating on the mobs. If they made it so the pet corpse was only lootable by the caster who conjured the pet, and let the pet corpse stay in the game as long as a player's corpse, there should be no problem in getting that weapon back to give to another pet.</P><P>Any input is greatly appreciated in advance.</P><P>---Gandalf the Wizard</P><P> </font></td>

