        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Only give pet weapons that you are willing to lose unless it's a charmed pet. Weapons do not matter to a pet and do not alter it's attack ratio or damage output in any way, twohanded or not. I'd only give pet weapons with a added effect like Yaks, Snare Whips, Swarmcaller, Truck of Doom,  etc.</P><P>Any claims of pet doing more damage with higher damage weapon can be disproven through the test of Weighted Axe. Atlered ratio remarks can be rejected through the test of using a crapilicious weapon and then comparing it to a priceless weapon. Parse your pet beating on a locked check with a two handed weapon and then give him 2 one handed weapons and damage will be about the same.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

