         Don't quote me on this because I have not been that level in a while, but as I recall, the lower level pets in that level range can dual wield *IF* you give them 2 1handed weapons.  Might be the level 20 pet, might be 24, but somewhere in there was a level range where pets would duel wield (swing more often basically) with 2 weapons.</P><P>I think it was 24 though, because it was the level when your pet would turn dark brown.  If I'm not mistaken, they later changed it to at level 29, your pet could OCCASIONALLY get dual wield automatically if it was a high enough level pet, and at 34 it was automatic.  Go to casters realm and look through the old patch messages.</P><P><BR><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107355" target="_blank">Those who have turned away, shall be turned upon. <br> Lich Ravanta Suffer</a>  <img src=icon_smile_evil.gif border=0 align=middle><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
